{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876980738,"sessionID":"ses_2857becffffeyHv4pl4FI5jlwY","part":{"id":"prt_d7a843358001mweoe3OcxO2f9F","messageID":"msg_d7a84259b001wLkPhDPNX2slaq","sessionID":"ses_2857becffffeyHv4pl4FI5jlwY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2565759ff9ce4306acaabab6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n2: \n3: **Module:** docker  \n4: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Directory & Base Dockerfile\n11: \n12: - [x] **T001** Create `docker/` directory at project root\n13: - [x] **T002** Create `docker/base.Dockerfile` with Go build environment\n14:   - Base image: `golang:1.24-alpine`\n15:   - Include go mod download\n16:   - Build stage named: `builder`\n17: - [x] **T003** Add build arguments to base.Dockerfile (GO_VERSION, BUILDER_IMAGE, RUNTIME_IMAGE, BINARY_VERSION)\n18: - [ ] **T004** Verify `docker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder -t agentcube-builder:test .` succeeds\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Phase 2: Router Dockerfile\n23: \n24: - [x] **T010** Create `docker/Dockerfile.router` with multi-stage build\n25: - [x] **T011** Builder stage copies source and builds router binary from `cmd/router/main.go`\n26: - [x] **T012** Runtime stage uses `alpine:3.19` as base\n27: - [x] **T013** Create non-root user `agentcube` (UID 1000)\n28: - [x] **T014** Copy binary from builder stage to `/usr/local/bin/router`\n29: - [x] **T015** Set correct file permissions (chmod +x)\n30: - [x] **T016** Configure ENTRYPOINT for router binary\n31: - [ ] **T017** Verify `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .` succeeds\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Phase 3: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n36: \n37: - [x] **T020** Create `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager` with multi-stage build\n38: - [x] **T021** Builder stage builds workload-manager binary from `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n39: - [x] **T022** Runtime stage uses `alpine:3.19` as base\n40: - [x] **T023** Create non-root user `agentcube` (UID 1000)\n41: - [x] **T024** Copy binary from builder stage to `/usr/local/bin/workload-manager`\n42: - [x] **T025** Set correct file permissions (chmod +x)\n43: - [x] **T026** Configure ENTRYPOINT for workload-manager binary\n44: - [ ] **T027** Verify `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:test .` succeeds\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## Phase 4: Agentd Dockerfile\n49: \n50: - [x] **T030** Create `docker/Dockerfile.agentd` with multi-stage build\n51: - [x] **T031** Builder stage builds agentd binary from `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n52: - [x] **T032** Builder stage builds picod binary from `cmd/picod/main.go`\n53: - [x] **T033** Runtime stage uses `alpine:3.19` as base\n54: - [x] **T034** Create non-root user `agentcube` (UID 1000)\n55: - [x] **T035** Copy both binaries from builder stage to `/usr/local/bin/`\n56: - [x] **T036** Set correct file permissions (chmod +x)\n57: - [x] **T037** Configure ENTRYPOINT for agentd binary (supports picod as argument)\n58: - [ ] **T038** Verify `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:test .` succeeds\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## Phase 5: Binary Execution Verification\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T040** Test router binary: `docker run --rm agentcube-router:test --help` exits 0\n65: - [ ] **T041** Test workload-manager binary: `docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager:test --help` exits 0\n66: - [ ] **T042** Test agentd binary: `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd:test --help` exits 0\n67: - [ ] **T043** Test picod binary: `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd:test picod --help` exits 0\n68: - [ ] **T044** Test router version: `docker run --rm agentcube-router:test version` exits 0\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Phase 6: Security Verification\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T050** Verify router runs as non-root: `docker run --rm agentcube-router:id` shows uid=1000\n75: - [ ] **T051** Verify workload-manager runs as non-root: `docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager:id` shows uid=1000\n76: - [ ] **T052** Verify agentd runs as non-root: `docker run --rm agentcube-agentd:id` shows uid=1000\n77: - [ ] **T053** Verify no source code in router: `docker run --rm agentcube-router ls /build` returns error\n78: - [ ] **T054** Verify no go.mod in router: `docker run --rm agentcube-router cat go.mod` returns error\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Phase 7: Image Size Verification\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T060** Check router image size: `docker images agentcube-router --format \"{{.Size}}\"` < 50MB\n85: - [ ] **T061** Check workload-manager image size: `docker images agentcube-workload-manager --format \"{{.Size}}\"` < 50MB\n86: - [ ] **T062** Check agentd image size: `docker images agentcube-agentd --format \"{{.Size}}\"` < 60MB\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Phase 8: Makefile Integration (Optional)\n91: \n92: - [x] **T070** Add docker-build-router target to Makefile\n93: - [x] **T071** Add docker-build-workload-manager target to Makefile\n94: - [x] **T072** Add docker-build-agentd target to Makefile\n95: - [x] **T073** Add docker-build (all) target to Makefile\n96: - [ ] **T074** Verify `make docker-build-router` succeeds\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Phase 9: Cache Reuse Verification\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T080** Run first build (cold): `time docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .`\n103: - [ ] **T081** Run second build (no changes): `time docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:test .`\n104: - [ ] **T082** Verify second build completes in < 30 seconds (cache reused)\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Dependencies\n109: \n110: ```\n111: T001 → T002 → T003 → T004\n112: T010-T017 (Router - depends on T002-T004)\n113: T020-T027 (Workload Manager - depends on T002-T004)\n114: T030-T038 (Agentd - depends on T002-T004)\n115: T040-T044 (Binary tests - depends on T017, T027, T038)\n116: T050-T054 (Security tests - depends on T040-T044)\n117: T060-T062 (Size tests - depends on T040-T044)\n118: T070-T074 (Makefile - can parallel after T040-T044)\n119: T080-T082 (Cache tests - depends on T017)\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **Parallel:** Phase 2, 3, 4 (Router, Workload Manager, Agentd Dockerfiles) can be done in parallel after Phase 1\n123: \n124: ## Acceptance Criteria\n125: \n126: - [x] `docker/base.Dockerfile` exists with Go builder stage\n127: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` builds successfully, image < 50MB\n128: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager` builds successfully, image < 50MB\n129: - [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.agentd` builds successfully, image < 60MB\n130: - [ ] All binaries execute correctly inside containers\n131: - [ ] All containers run as non-root (uid=1000)\n132: - [ ] No source code present in runtime images\n133: - [ ] Build cache works correctly (second build < 30s)\n134: \n135: ## Verification Commands\n136: \n137: ```bash\n138: # Build all images\n139: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:latest .\n140: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:latest .\n141: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:latest .\n142: \n143: # Binary verification\n144: docker run --rm agentcube-router version\n145: docker run --rm agentcube-workload-manager --help\n146: docker run --rm agentcube-agentd --help\n147: docker run --rm agentcube-agentd picod --help\n148: \n149: # Security verification\n150: docker run --rm agentcube-router id\n151: docker run --rm agentcube-router ls /build\n152: \n153: # Size verification\n154: docker images agentcube-router\n155: docker images agentcube-workload-manager\n156: docker images agentcube-agentd\n157: ```\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n**Module:** docker  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Directory & Base Dockerfile\n\n- [x] **T001** Create `docker/` directory at project root\n- [x] **T002** Create `docker/base.Dockerfile` with Go build environment\n  - Base image: `golang:1.24-alpine`\n  - Include go mod download\n  - Build stage named: `builder`\n- [x] **T003** Add build arguments to base.Dockerfile (GO_VERSION, BUILDER_IMAGE, RUNTIME_IMAGE, BINARY_VERSION)\n- [ ] **T004** Verify `docker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder -t agentcube-builder:test .` succeeds\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775876980714,"end":1775876980736}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876980742,"sessionID":"ses_2857becffffeyHv4pl4FI5jlwY","part":{"id":"prt_d7a843721001fVbknXEAPu6Tz6","messageID":"msg_d7a84259b001wLkPhDPNX2slaq","sessionID":"ses_2857becffffeyHv4pl4FI5jlwY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1bd5ce09d69247039ed8b83a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775876980718,"end":1775876980740}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876980744,"sessionID":"ses_2857becffffeyHv4pl4FI5jlwY","part":{"id":"prt_d7a843b7f001w3MxwZm2nckcnB","messageID":"msg_d7a84259b001wLkPhDPNX2slaq","sessionID":"ses_2857becffffeyHv4pl4FI5jlwY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5e772a98144e474e934357ac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775876980721,"end":1775876980742}}}}
